rComments: Pros: - Material really similar to BPS2110 so if you have taken it, the course is just a refresher - Dr. Ben is one of the nicest profs you will ever meet. He really cares about the students and easily accessible outside and during class as well - 2 Midterms and a Final that are pretty straight forward with no surprises Cons: Memorization heavy
Good lectures. Class is all orgo though!
Great Professor! Really cares about his students.

Ben pretty much tells you what will be on the exam before you write it. He writes his notes out on the screen while he lectures. No textbook so only need to study what he says in class. Memorization heavy but easy 10

So happy I took this course with Dr. Ben! Great way to finish my undergrad degree. The two midterms were carbon copies of the lecture notes. The final will make you think a bit; testing for this class was extremely fair as long as you go to class + copy the notes. He's a phenomenal lecturer and is always available to help. Best 4th year BCH course.

The class is about organic synthesis. He spoke to higher level PhD Biochemistry students and I was feeling stressed and left behind. However, he made himself available and helped before the exams. He did not come to the final exam. He did not reply to emails either. His guest lecture was terrible, she just dumped on us everything she knew and left.

Definitely was way harder than I anticipated. No multiple choice questions, all short or long answer questions, which really isnt for me. Lots of memorization is required since there are no multiple choices. However, he did post the exam questions online but he had titled them as "practice questions", so study those!

Pros: No textbook, no homework or at-home assignments.   Cons: Hard marker. Exams did not reflect what was in his notes (includes things that were never taught). Expectations were unclear. Lectures were not very stimulating.
This is the worst teacher I have ever had. Nothing was explained properly. Very difficult grader.
Do not make the same mistake I did and take this class as an elective.

This guy is a really good prof. His lectures were never boring and his notes were clear. The only annoying thing was that he didn't post his lecture notes online but he was always available to clarify concepts. Kind of wish he was teaching the whole semester

He is AMAZING. I've never felt so involved in a course. He really tries to make the material as interesting as possible. His midterm was so easy but the TAs were awful at marking it because they were all short answer. If you read the notes daily, then you will succeed in his portion of the course. I'm not too fond about 2nd part.
Great Professor and lecturer who really does care about the students in his class.  He taught the first half of the course and I wish he was teaching the entire course!

Very good lecturer. Is funny and keeps it interesting.   Biggest issue : he told us "to focus on key concepts" across his first 6 lectures (2nd half of course). Midterm: 1575 marks were pure number recall. Over half of the questions were from lectures 12, very little from lec 56. Very unfair.   Knowing his midterm though, the final was fair.

Going to class is helpful, but not super bad if you skip a class. He does post his PowerPoint slides but only AFTER the lecture so be prepared to take notes on a laptoptablet. Very funny, entertaining. Midterms not hard, but you need to know a broad spectrum of the course material because never puts what he says he will on the midterm. Good prof!

Really bad teacher. Does not help students and does not care about. Terrible class, never take anything with him. He always lie when asked about marks. He does not keep his word and do not follow deadlines.
Amazing Prof. Go to his office hours. Talk to him. Listen to him. Wish more were like him. Very Fair. Very smart. Great teacher. Great tests. A+
He's a really good prof. Explains things well and his midterms and final are very fair. He does get off topic a lot but for the most part he's great!
Fairest of all organic classes. If you got A+ in the first 2, A+ in this class should be no problem.

Dr Ben is fantastic. His classes are fun and interesting, and his love of the material is contagious. He conveys it well, encourages a LOT of thinking and class participation, and makes sure you understand the material. He's very available outside of class, in office hours/email, and he seems to really care about students.
He's a good prof, but tends to go off-topic a lot...I wish that he had focussed more on what we actually needed to know, and less on random drug syntheses.
Ballin'

Dr Ben is the most amazing prof i have ever had..A class like organic Chem where not a lot of ppl like to take but if someone like Dr Ben is teaching you start loving organic..His lectures are very interesting..I always looked forward to his class..He is very helpful and approchable..He actually cares for student not just does it job and leaves.

Dr. Ben is one of the best organic profs around. Not only is he clear but makes organic interesting. The midterms and final were both fair. The only downside is his teaching is slow paced in the beginning but the last two weeks of classes were brutal. Great prof if you ever get the chance take his course. "When you wake up you'd better be running."
Explains things well. Approachable. Tries to incorporate interesting topics into organic chemistry. Overall he is one of the best professors I've had.

Go to his office hours, get there early cause his office gets full, but he'll explain things differently then he does in class, and it helps to understand. He definitely wants to help and make sure you get it, plus he makes his classes interesting with a lot of funny anecdotes about his lab misfortunes, its pretty entertaining.
He was interesting, but a lot of material was shoved into the last two weeks of the course... the exam was hard.
He loves organic and teaches it well.  Present during his office hours to answer questions.  Midterms and final are fair, must know your mechanisms well!

Completely useless as a prof.  His lectures consisted entirely of writing almost word for word, what was in the textbook, on the blackboard, which most of us couldn't see anyways because of the size and lighting of the lecture room.
He knows a lot, but does not know how to teach well. Acts to be really friendly in class during lectures, but is downright mean when you go to see him private. Too snobby for a prof.

Unclear and ambiguous lectures.  Course is "Applications in Spectroscopy"  and we do nothing but theory in class.  Prof very unhelpful and condescending.  Very rude to students who wait hours to see him (even with an appointment!)
Midterms are hard and markers are picky.
Very clear at explaining organic chemistry. Excellent prof and reasonable too!!
good prof but is not available for students much for questions
No Comments
Great Prof! Makes Spec a lot more interesting. Reasonable mid-terms.
No Comments
